Probabilistic Methods, Reinforcement Learning, Theory. 

Probabilistic Methods: The paper deals with partially observable Markov decision processes (pomdps), which are probabilistic models.

Reinforcement Learning: The paper discusses dynamic-programming updates, which are a crucial operation in a wide range of pomdp solution methods, including reinforcement learning.

Theory: The paper examines the problem of performing exact dynamic-programming updates in pomdps from a computational complexity viewpoint and offers a new algorithm, called the witness algorithm, which can compute updated value functions efficiently on a restricted class of pomdps.
